# Sample pass:// references — copy to .env (kept git-ignored) and adjust.
#
# Values are *references* to Proton Pass items, not secrets: `pass-cli run
# --env-file .env -- <cmd>` resolves them at run time and injects the real
# values only into <cmd>'s environment (masked in stdout/stderr).
#
# References are ID-based — pass://SHARE_ID/ITEM_ID/FIELD — vault or item
# *names* in the URI do not resolve (pass-cli passes them through untouched).
# Look the IDs up after `.devcontainer/pass-relogin` with:
#   pass-cli item list --vault-name <vault> --output json   # -> share_id, id
# IDs are opaque identifiers, safe to have in this committed sample; the real
# .env stays ignored as insurance against pasting an actual token into it.
#
# With a per-project vault (PAT file ~/.config/proton-pass-agent/<dir name>; see
# README "Task secrets"), mint the refs from that vault's item IDs instead.
# The item title `github-fine-grained` is a fixed convention —
# .devcontainer/pass-relogin seeds gh auth from it in whatever vault the PAT can see.

# GitHub fine-grained PAT (gh CLI / git push)
GITHUB_TOKEN=pass://<SHARE_ID>/<ITEM_ID>/token
GH_TOKEN=pass://<SHARE_ID>/<ITEM_ID>/token

# Generic API keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=pass://<SHARE_ID>/<ITEM_ID>/api-key
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=pass://<SHARE_ID>/<ITEM_ID>/api-token
